---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  title="About | Dr. Haitham A. El-Ghareeb"
  description="A provisional scholarly profile for Dr. Haitham A. El-Ghareeb"
>
  <main class="page-main">
    <section class="shell hero">
      <p class="hero__eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="hero__title">Dr. Haitham A. El-Ghareeb</h1>
      <p class="hero__lead">
        A scholar and academic building a structured digital presence around scholarly identity,
        publications, critical editions, articles, and research-facing intellectual work, with a
        strong emphasis on Islamic studies and organized knowledge presentation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="shell section">
      <div class="grid-two">
        <article class="content-card">
          <p class="content-card__meta">Profile</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">A scholarly website with a clear purpose</h2>
          <p>
            This website is intended to serve as a central reference point for biography, books,
            critical editions, articles, and future scholarly projects in a unified bilingual format.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="content-card">
          <p class="content-card__meta">Aim</p>
          <h2 class="section-title">Why this platform exists</h2>
          <p>
            Its purpose is to gather academic and intellectual work in one place and present it
            in an orderly, modern, and expandable digital structure.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="shell section">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="section-kicker">Current research-facing themes</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Interests reflected in the current project plan</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-three">
        <article class="feature-card">
          <h3>Islamic Studies</h3>
          <p>A central theme in the planned structure and scholarly direction of the site.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <h3>Critical Editing and Manuscripts</h3>
          <p>A dedicated space is reserved for editorial and manuscript-related scholarly work.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <h3>Defense of Sunnah</h3>
          <p>One of the specialized intellectual areas highlighted in the broader site vision.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <h3>AI and Islamic Heritage</h3>
          <p>A forward-looking theme connecting contemporary tools with heritage scholarship.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <h3>E-Learning in Islamic Studies</h3>
          <p>An interest in structured educational delivery and scholarly digital communication.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-card">
          <h3>Articles and Projects</h3>
          <p>The site is designed to support ongoing publication and documented scholarly initiatives.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
